{
  "texts": [
    "Three high-performing models achieved 70-74% disclosure: DeepSeek-V3, Qwen3-235B-Inst, and GPT-OSS-20B.",
    "In contrast, three low-performing models showed 3-14% disclosure through most prompts: Llama-3.1-8B-Inst, Llama-3.3-70B-Inst, and Mistral-Small-3.2-24B-Inst.",
    "The existence of models achieving over 70% disclosure demonstrates that significant improvement is possible with existing training approaches, though no model approaches baseline honesty.Within narrow parameter ranges, model identity explains dramatic performance differences.",
    "Models spanning 8B to 70B parameters achieve comparable low disclosure rates of 2.8-4.1%, while Disclosure rates for all models across personas.",
    "Professional personas suppress disclosure across all tested models compared to baseline personas."
  ]
}